          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a Hindu philosophical treatise and commentary, reflecting on the Māṇḍūkyopaniṣad, a late Vedic text that focuses Hindu mantras (words or phrases of power), especially the mantra Oṃ, while also outlining four states of consciousness (awake, dreaming, sleeping, and transcendent).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Māṇḍūkyopaniṣaddīpikā</title>
              <title type="vernacular">माण्डूक्योपनिषद्दीपिका</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Śaṅkarānanda, active 1290</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīmatparamahaṃsaparivrājakācāryānaṃdātmapūjyapādaśiṣyasya śrīśaṃkarānaṃde bhagavataḥ kṛti māṃdūkyopaniṣddīpikā samāptā // (f. 5r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
